com.bluegosling.result

Class Result<T,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.result.Result<T,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of value, for successful results
    E - the type of error, for failed results (typically, but not necessarily, a sub-type of Throwable)
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @ValueType
public final class Result<T,E>
extends Object
implements Serializable
    The result of an operation, which can either represent a successful value or a cause of failure.

    In some respects, this is like a Future, except the result is available immediately. In other respects, it is like an Optional with extra information (cause of failure) when the value is not present. Its API has similarities with both Optional and FluentFuture.

      • asFuture

        public FluentFuture<T> asFuture()
        Returns a future that represents the same value or failure as this result. If this result represents a failure then the future will be a failed future. In that case, if the cause of failure is a Throwable, that is is the cause of failure for the returned future, too. Otherwise, the cause of failure for the future is a FailedResultException that wraps the result's cause of failure.
        Returns:
        a future that represents the same value or failure as this result

      • asPossible

        public Possible<T> asPossible()
        Returns the result's value, as a possible. If this is a failed result, this returns an empty/unset value. Otherwise, the returned possible value holds the result's value. Unlike asOptional(), a possible can represent a successful null value and is thus distinguishable from the possible value of a failed result.
        Returns:
        a possible values that represents this result's value
